This paper discusses abstractive summarization approaches based on Reinforcement Learning (RL) and proposes alternative evaluation measures. The topic of abstractive summarization falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL. The use of RL and alternative evaluation measures also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper mentions improvements in automated metrics, which could indicate a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) commonly used in NLP tasks.
